<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBBFFC6FF37FC35E391FB88" blockId="3.[151,754,1012,1036]" box="[151,754,1012,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">
<typeStatus id="94338867FFBBFFC6FF37FC35E1AAFB88" box="[151,201,1012,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBBFFC6FE86FC35E088FB88" authority="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch, 2022" authorityName="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch" authorityYear="2022" box="[294,491,1012,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chlorosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bele" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBBFFC6FE86FC35E088FB88" box="[294,491,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Chlorosphecia bele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62CF57ACFFBBFFC6FE51FC35E321FB8F" box="[497,578,1012,1035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, designated here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0392654EFFBBFFC6FF37FBF8E2A5F884" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" type="description">
<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBBFFC6FF37FBF8E2ABFA64" blockId="3.[151,1437,1081,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBBFFC6FF37FBF8E04AFBD7" bold="true" box="[151,297,1081,1107]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Description.</emphasis>
Head: haustellum well developed and surely functional; labial palpus long and thin, upward curved, with tip protruding over base of antenna; first palpomere short, second and third palpomeres very long, smoothly scaled, second palpomere ventrally and distally slightly rough with some bristle-like scales distally; frons smooth and glossy; vertex glossy, scales predominantly broad and smooth, laterally and occipitally narrow, but not hair-like, with strong shine; antenna clavate, middle part slightly narrowed, extending just distal of discal spot of forewing, ciliate, ciliae longest at flagellum base, tapering distally. Thorax: narrow, smoothly scaled, without hair-like scales. Legs: strong, mostly smoothly scaled; tibiae partially with long, rough scales, especially on middle and distal parts of hind tibia; hindleg somewhat elongated, protruding beyond abdomen. Wings: hyaline; forewing apical area present, with short basad-pointing protrusions between medius veins; discal spots well developed; forewing veins R 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FADAFAADE4E1FAFE" attach="left" box="[1402,1410,1388,1402]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">1</subScript>
to R 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FF0AFA51E1D1FA1A" attach="left" box="[170,178,1424,1438]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">3</subScript>
as well as CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FEFDFA51E006FA1A" attach="left" box="[349,357,1424,1438]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FE6EFA51E0B5FA1A" attach="left" box="[462,470,1424,1438]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">2</subScript>
running very close, R 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FD6AFA51E3B1FA1A" attach="left" box="[714,722,1424,1438]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">4</subScript>
and R 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FCB9FA51E242FA1A" attach="left" box="[793,801,1424,1438]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">5</subScript>
with short common stalk; hindwing vein M 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FAA6FA51E46DFA1A" attach="left" box="[1286,1294,1424,1438]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">2</subScript>
arising from caudal part of discocellular vein, CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FDE4FA75E32FFA46" attach="left" box="[580,588,1460,1474]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FD18FA75E3A3FA46" attach="left" box="[696,704,1460,1474]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">2</subScript>
arising from common point. Abdomen: strongly tapered distally, shorter than hindlegs, with laterally flattened anal tuft. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBBFFC6FF67FA2BE2A5F884" blockId="3.[151,1437,1081,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBBFFC6FF67FA2BE010F987" bold="true" box="[199,371,1513,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D3B32A40FFBBFFC6FE24FA2BE0A8F980" box="[388,459,1514,1540]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[208,1380,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Genitalia structure and segment eight of Synanthedonini. 3. Nimbamina blei Sáfián &amp; Bartsch sp. nov., holotype ♂ (vesica double the size). 4. Chlorosphecia bele Bartsch &amp; Sáfián sp. nov., holotype ♂. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577750/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Tegumen slender, somewhat shorter than uncus, with short, pointed gnathos basally, almost completely fused with uncus forming a narrow, long segment; uncus long, distally pointed, ventro-lateral edges densely covered with long, bifurcate, basad-pointing setae. Juxta extremely short, forming a narrow, transverse band. Valva elongate, narrow, dorsal margin slightly rounded and ventral margin straight, apically broadly rounded, crista sacculi short, densely covered with strongly sclerotised setae, inner surface in dorso-distal half covered with long, strong, bifurcate setae that become distinctly smaller dorso-distally; an area of very long and strong setae dorsal to crista sacculi, distal half of ventral margin with dense simple setae. Saccus short. Phallus straight, basally broad, largely membranous, distally very narrow, without thorns.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0392654EFFBBFFC0FF67F8C8E3E0FD2D" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBBFFC6FF67F8C8E515F830" blockId="3.[151,1437,1081,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBBFFC6FF67F8C8E021F8A7" bold="true" box="[199,322,1801,1827]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBBFFC6FEE9F8CBE08EF8A0" authority="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch, 2022" authorityName="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,493,1802,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chlorosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBBFFC6FEE9F8CBE08EF8A0" box="[329,493,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Chlorosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBBFFC6FE55F8CBE33CF8A0" bold="true" box="[501,607,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62CF57ACFFBBFFC6FE55F8CBE33CF8A0" box="[501,607,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is defined as follows: (1) labial palpus long, upturned; (2) hindwing vein M 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FF10F881E1DBF8CA" attach="left" box="[176,184,1856,1870]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">2</subScript>
arising from caudal part of discocellular vein, CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FD5BF881E260F8CA" attach="left" box="[763,771,1856,1870]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBBFFC6FCCFF881E214F8CA" attach="left" box="[879,887,1856,1870]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">2</subScript>
arising from common point; (3) uncus with ventro-lateral rows of setae instead of scopula androconialis; (4) gnathos at base of tegumen, short, pointed; (5) valva narrow, distally rounded, with small crista sacculi; (6) juxta extremely short; (7) phallus basally broad, distally very slender. We consider characters (2), (4) and (5) to be diagnostic characters for the genus.
</paragraph>
<caption id="1FF7664DFFBCFFC1FF37F856E580F857" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577750" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6577750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577750/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" startId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[208,1380,181,1920]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBCFFC1FF37F856E580F857" blockId="4.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBCFFC1FF37F856E058F82B" bold="true" box="[151,315,1943,1967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">FIGURES 3–4.</emphasis>
Genitalia structure and segment eight of 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBCFFC1FD41F859E2E0F834" authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[737,899,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synanthedonini">Synanthedonini</taxonomicName>
. 3. 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBCFFC1FC08F859E462F834" authority="Safian &amp; Bartsch" authorityName="Safian &amp; Bartsch" authorityYear="2022" box="[936,1281,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Nimbamina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBCFFC1FC08F859E528F834" box="[936,1099,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Nimbamina blei</emphasis>
Sáfián &amp; Bartsch
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBCFFC1FAA8F859E43AF834" bold="true" box="[1288,1369,1944,1968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62CF57ACFFBCFFC1FAA8F859E43AF834" box="[1288,1369,1944,1968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype ♂ (vesica double the size). 4. 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBCFFC1FE57F87DE212F850" authority="Bartsch &amp; Safian" authorityName="Bartsch &amp; Safian" authorityYear="2022" box="[503,881,1980,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chlorosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bele" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBCFFC1FE57F87DE3DFF850" box="[503,700,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Chlorosphecia bele</emphasis>
Bartsch &amp; Sáfián
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBCFFC1FCD7F87DE2A4F850" bold="true" box="[887,967,1980,2004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62CF57ACFFBCFFC1FCD7F87DE2A4F850" box="[887,967,1980,2004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype ♂. Scales: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBDFFC0FF67FF56E519FE29" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">
Based on the structure of the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FD17FF56E238FF35" authority="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch, 2022" authorityName="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch" authorityYear="2022" box="[695,859,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chlorosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FD17FF56E238FF35" box="[695,859,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Chlorosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FCC2FF56E2A9FF35" bold="true" box="[866,970,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62CF57ACFFBDFFC0FCC2FF56E2A9FF35" box="[866,970,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears to be related to a group of genera which have scopula androconialis undeveloped, gnathos large and shifted down to base of tegumen, and valva with weakly sclerotised distal part, namely 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FDE5FF1EE2E5FF7D" authority="Hampson, 1900" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1900" box="[581,902,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Lepidopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FDE5FF1EE3A8FF7D" box="[581,715,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Lepidopoda</emphasis>
Hampson, 1900
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FC31FF1EE590FF7D" authority="Le Cerf, 1916" authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1916" box="[913,1267,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Macrotarsipodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FC31FF1EE52CFF7D" box="[913,1103,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Macrotarsipodes</emphasis>
Le Cerf, 1916
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FA89FF1EE0FEFE99" authority="Hampson, [1893]" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Macrotarsipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FA89FF1EE1B2FE98" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Macrotarsipus</emphasis>
Hampson, [1893]
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FE0DFEC2E307FE9A" authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[429,612,259,286]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synanthedonini">Synanthedonini</taxonomicName>
). Externally, all these genera clearly differ from 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FB27FEC2E448FE99" authority="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch, 2022" authorityName="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch" authorityYear="2022" box="[1159,1323,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chlorosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FB27FEC2E448FE99" box="[1159,1323,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Chlorosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FA92FEC2E4FFFE99" bold="true" box="[1330,1436,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62CF57ACFFBDFFC0FA92FEC2E4FFFE99" box="[1330,1436,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the venation of the hindwing, with M 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBDFFC0FDF8FEF8E303FEC3" attach="left" box="[600,608,313,327]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">2</subScript>
arising from the costal one third of the discocellular vein and a short common stalk of CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBDFFC0FEC1FE9CE00AFEEF" attach="left" box="[353,361,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBDFFC0FE76FE9CE0BDFEEF" attach="left" box="[470,478,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">2</subScript>
. The latter two genera further differ by the elongated hindlegs. In the male genitalia, the three genera we are here comparing to the new genus have gnathos much larger, valva broader without crista sacculi and a dense, dorsal area of setae, and phallus basally narrower and distally wider.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBDFFC0FF67FE76E3E0FD2D" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">
Superficially, 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FEC6FE76E369FE55" authority="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch, 2022" authorityName="Sáfián &amp; Bartsch" authorityYear="2022" box="[358,522,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chlorosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FEC6FE76E369FE55" box="[358,522,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Chlorosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FDB3FE76E31EFE55" bold="true" box="[531,637,439,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62CF57ACFFBDFFC0FDB3FE76E31EFE55" box="[531,637,439,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FC22FE76E5A9FE55" authority="Aurivillius, 1905" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1905" box="[898,1226,438,465]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Episannina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FC22FE76E561FE54" box="[898,1026,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Episannina</emphasis>
Aurivillius, 1905
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FB7AFE76E4F2FE56" authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[1242,1425,439,466]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synanthedonini">Synanthedonini</taxonomicName>
). However, it clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FE5EFE1AE31DFE70" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1905" box="[510,638,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Episannina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FE5EFE1AE31DFE70" box="[510,638,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Episannina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer labial palpus, the broader forewing discal spot, the longer hindwing discal spot, the hindwing venation (M 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBDFFC0FD16FDD0E3DDFD9B" attach="left" box="[694,702,529,543]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">2</subScript>
arising from costal one third of discocellular vein and CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBDFFC0FAC4FDD0E40FFD9B" attach="left" box="[1380,1388,529,543]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="D70C3480FFBDFFC0FF6CFDF4E1B7FDC7" attach="left" box="[204,212,565,579]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">2</subScript>
with common stalk in 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FE75FDE2E336FDB8" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1905" box="[469,597,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Episannina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FE75FDE2E336FDB8" box="[469,597,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Episannina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the shape of the hindleg scale tufts (larger, broad and flat, extending over entire length of hind tibia in 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FE78FD86E33BFDE4" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1905" box="[472,600,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Episannina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FE78FD86E33BFDE4" box="[472,600,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Episannina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the completely different structure of the male genitalia (egg. scopula androconialis well developed, gnathos small, distally located, valva broader, without crista sacculi and bald areas in 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FF37FD4EE074FD2C" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,279,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Episannina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FF37FD4EE074FD2C" box="[151,279,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Episannina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation id="2F194B34FFBDFFC0FE24FD4EE31BFD2D" author="Bartsch, D. &amp; Berg, J." box="[388,632,655,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" pagination="28 - 46" refId="ref3996" refString="Bartsch, D. &amp; Berg, J. (2012) New species and review of the Afrotropical clearwing moth genus Camaegeria Strand, 1914 (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae: Synanthedonini). Zootaxa, 3181, 28 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3181.1.2" type="journal article" year="2012">Bartsch &amp; Berg 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0392654EFFBDFFC0FF67FD73E5E9FD75" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4B3736C5FFBDFFC0FF67FD73E5E9FD75" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FF67FD73E0C5FD48" bold="true" box="[199,422,690,716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Derivatio nominis.</emphasis>
From the ancient Greek χλωρός (“chloros” = light green) and σφηξ (“Sphex” = wasp); - 
<emphasis id="79FCEAD7FFBDFFC0FF37FD16E18EFD75" box="[151,237,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">sphecia</emphasis>
is a commonly used ending of genera within the 
<taxonomicName id="8C884D46FFBDFFC0FCB5FD16E215FD75" authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[789,886,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sesiidae</taxonomicName>
. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
